replies.body:
I feel shaco should be played and built depending on the flow of the game and shouldn't really be a set thing. That said that build you posted seems kinda inefficient. Frozen mallet's slow won't stack with shaco e's passive slow and so is very gold innefficient, warrior is better considering shaco needs early burst and bloodrazor is for champions that stack atk speed or have alot of aa resets like udyr, warwick,jax and shyvanna, not for bursty assassins and even if you were going for atk speed shaco which is ok you had no other atk speed items. Titanic is not as bursty as ravenous hydra and is also more for tanks which would be fine if you went tank shaco but you have 1 hp item which doesn't get you alot of value out of it.
